Dr. Jill Biden delivered a commencement speech at Broward College in Fort Lauderdale, Florida. She congratulated the graduates and shared her experiences as a teacher and her visits to community colleges across the country. She emphasized the transformative power of education and the hope it brings to individuals of all ages and backgrounds. Dr. Biden also shared three lessons she has learned: lift up others, go to your strength, and never stop learning. She highlighted the inspiring stories of some of the graduates and encouraged them to continue making a positive impact in their communities. Dr. Biden closed her speech by urging the graduates to reflect on their achievements, celebrate with loved ones, and pursue their dreams with determination.